<div1 type="letter" n="1880-05-26">
<head>Letter from C. H. Crane to Walter Reed, May 26, 1880</head>
<pb n="1" id="f01776001"/>
<opener>
2260&sol;1880<lb/>
S. G. O. <dateline>
<date value="1880-05-26">May 26&sol;80</date>
</dateline><lb/>
Lieut. Walter Reed,<lb/>
Asst. Surgeon USA<lb/>
<unclear>Exchange</unclear> Hotel,<lb/>
Richmond, Va<lb/>
<salute>Sir:</salute>
</opener>
<p>In reply to your letter of the 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi><lb/>
instant, I have to inform you that<lb/>
an application from you, for a leave<lb/>
of absence for one month with<lb/>
permission to apply for an extension<lb/>
of two months, will be approved by<lb/>
the Surgeon General.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Very respectfully</salute>
<signed><unclear>[unclear]</unclear><lb/>
<unclear>C.H.C.</unclear></signed>
</closer>
</div1>
</body>
